HEADWORD: Optime
<hw>Op"ti*me</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., adv. fr.
<ets>optimus</ets> the best.]</ety> <def>One of those who stand in the
second rank of honors, immediately after the wranglers, in the
University of Cambridge, England. They are divided into senior and
junior optimes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

